        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "All-uses testing: The test set includes at least one path from every definition to every use that can be reached by that definition.",
                "img_id": null
            },
            {
                "type": "img",
                "content": null,
                "img_id": "img0_se_theory_practice.pdf__chunk_3381_3386_813"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "All-uses testing is a stronger testing strategy than statement testing because it covers more paths and interactions between variable definitions and uses.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "To test code thoroughly, we can choose test cases using at least one of several approaches based on the data manipulated by the code: Statement testing ... All-uses testing ...",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "All-uses testing requires more test cases than statement testing because it must cover all paths from every variable definition to every use, whereas statement testing only requires each statement to be executed once.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Statement testing: Every statement in the component is executed at least once in some test.",
