        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Documents. Formal documentation accompanies every system and supports training. The documents contain all the information needed to use the system properly and efficiently.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "These documents exist in separate manuals or online and are accessible to users and operators as the system is functioning.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Existing in separate manuals or online, documents are accessible to users and operators as the system is functioning.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Users may also benefit from well-defined icons, online help, demonstrations, and classes to learn how the system works, especially since many users do not read manuals thoroughly.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "In this and many other cases, users may prefer well-defined icons, online help, demonstrations, and classes to learn how the system works.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The system can be designed with an interface using icons to depict system functions, making training simpler for users by allowing them to scan icons rather than recall commands and syntax.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Icons and Online Help. A system can be designed so that its interface with the user makes system functions clear and easy to understand. Most computer-based systems follow the example of Apple and Xerox in using icons to depict a user's choice of system functions. A click of the mouse selects an icon, and a second click invokes the function. Training for such systems is relatively simple, since the functions are more easily remembered by scanning the icons than by recalling commands and syntax.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Operators, like users, have access to the same documentation and training resources, which are designed to meet the varying needs of different audiences including users, operators, customers, programmers, and others who interact with the system.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "all training and documentation modules and documents should take into account the varying needs of different audiences: users, operators, customers, programmers, and others who work with or interact with the system",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Documentation is tailored to different audiences, so operators receive descriptions and information relevant to their role, which may differ from what users need.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Similarly, descriptions needed by operators are of no importance to a user.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    }
]

[
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Training aids and resources useful for users with little or no computer experience include formal documentation, icons, online help, and demonstrations or classes.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Documents. Formal documentation accompanies every system and supports training. The documents contain all the information needed to use the system properly and efficiently.",
                "img_id": null
            },
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "In fact, one study showed that only 10% to 15% of the users in an intensive training program read the manual at all. In this and many other cases, users may prefer well-defined icons, online help, demonstrations, and classes to learn how the system works.",
                "img_id": null
            },
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Icons and Online Help. A system can be designed so that its interface with the user makes system functions clear and easy to understand. Most computer-based systems follow the example of Apple and Xerox in using icons to depict a user's choice of system functions.",
                "img_id": null
            },
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Similarly, online help makes training easier. The user can scan additional information about a function's purpose or use without having to take the time to search through paper documents.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Examples of documentation meant for novice users include introductory books or manuals designed specifically for beginners.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "For example, the S-PLUS package (version 3.0, from MathSoft, Seattle, Washington) came with several books, including Read Me First. Each book is designed for a different audience and has a different purpose. Read Me First begins with a Documentation Roadmap, describing in four brief pages each of the other books included in the documentation: A Gentle Introduction to S-PLUS for the novice computer user.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    }
]

[
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "For system functions that are rarely executed by users or operators, review training is appropriate to help them remember the procedures after long intervals without use.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "If one system function is the semiannual storage of archival material on a separate disk, the operator may not remember the archive procedure after not having performed it for six months. Without review training, users and operators tend to perform only the functions with which they feel comfortable; they may not use other system functions that can make them more efficient and productive.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Additionally, specialized training courses can be designed for those who have special needs related to certain system functions, allowing training to focus on limited system functions or parts of the total system activity.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Similarly, specialized training courses can be designed for those who have special needs. If a system produces charts and reports, some users may need to know how to create the charts and reports, whereas others only want to access existing ones. Training can teach limited system functions or review just part of the total system activity.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    }
]

