[
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "A paper describing an organization's practical experience with a particular technology typically measures success by evaluating whether the technology solves the intended problem, its commercial viability, and the time it takes for the technology to become accepted practice.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "To know whether a technology is successful, we want to look at whether it solves a problem, whether it is commercially viable, and how long it takes for the technology to become accepted practice.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The kinds of evidence presented to support the evaluation of effectiveness include surveys, case studies, experiments, feature analysis, and other techniques that examine the technology itself and the body of evidence to assess whether it forms a compelling argument for using the technology.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "We want to know how 'solid' a case we have for believing that the new technology will solve the business problem it addresses. This growing body of evidence should then be subjected to a more advanced evaluation, where we examine not only the technology but also the evidence itself. That is, to assess whether the body of evidence forms a compelling argument for using the technology, we look at the situations in which the technology has been used, compare the old ways to the new ways, and determine (using surveys, case studies, experiments, feature analysis, and other techniques) whether the evidence is conflicting, consistent, and objective.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "According to the categories of evidence proposed by Schum, the evidence can be classified based on the audience's interests: innovators focus on the technology itself, early adopters on the broader product, and the mainstream market on the company and market aspects. Different types of adopters rely on different communication channels and look for different attributes such as relative advantage in technology, product, company, and market.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Figure 14.2 summarizes the types of evidence appealing to different audiences. The lower-left quadrant reflects innovators' interests, where the focus is primarily on the technology itself. Early adopters turn their attention to the broader notion of product, while mainstream market members are more interested in the company and the market.",
                "img_id": null
            },
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "The nature of the communication channels used to increase awareness and knowledge of the technology. Some types of adopters find some communication channels more credible than others. Innovators tend to rely on technical journals and reports from researchers and technical experts. Early adopters in turn ask the innovators to confirm a technology's credibility. Early- and late-majority members ask others in their social system, often by word of mouth or benchmarking visits.",
                "img_id": null
            },
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Rogers suggests that the relevant attributes are Relative advantage: To what degree is the new technology better than what is already available? Innovators answer this question in technical terms: is it faster, architecturally superior, or more maintainable? Early adopters look for tangible evidence about the 'whole product.' Early-majority adopters seek information about the impact on the company, while late-majority adopters look at how the technology will increase market share.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    }
]

