            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "When working on the development system, we add functions to the current production or operational system to form the new development system. While a system is in production, problems may occur and be reported to us. Thus, a development system often serves two purposes: it adds the functionality of the next phase, and it corrects the problems found in previous versions. A development system can therefore involve adding new components as well as changing existing ones. However, this procedure allows faults to be introduced to components that have already been tested.",
