[
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The Mean Magnitude of Relative Error (MMRE) is calculated as the average of the absolute values of the relative errors for each project estimate.",
        "citations": []
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "For each project, the relative error is calculated as |Estimate - Actual| / Actual.",
        "citations": []
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Calculations for each project are as follows: A: |8060 - 8000| / 8000 = 60 / 8000 = 0.0075, B: |9000 - 10000| / 10000 = 1000 / 10000 = 0.1, C: |7000 - 7200| / 7200 = 200 / 7200 ≈ 0.0278, D: |15000 - 13000| / 13000 = 2000 / 13000 ≈ 0.1538, E: |10000 - 9600| / 9600 = 400 / 9600 ≈ 0.0417.",
        "citations": []
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The MMRE is the mean of these values: (0.0075 + 0.1 + 0.0278 + 0.1538 + 0.0417) / 5 = 0.06616, which rounds to 0.07.",
        "citations": []
    },
    {
        "role": "sentence",
        "segment": "Therefore, the MMRE for Jenna's estimating technique is 0.07.",
        "citations": []
    }
]

