        "segment": "Madeline uses the basic Walston and Felix model for effort estimation, which is given by the equation E = 5.25 * S^0.91, where S is the size of the system in lines of code.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Walston and Felix (1977) developed one of the first models of this type, finding that IBM data from 60 projects yielded an equation of the form ... E = 5.25 S 0.91",
